{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"98315d51-cd33-40fe-ba64-5164d093e6ba","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_GY38PAhkm8qtVLYOCI1E8d","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-363ef935f2204c6db6a76888eb181051/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-363ef935f2204c6db6a76888eb181051/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"539a63cf-8003-4a13-ac78-9d9a888da1b4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, which means it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, the build will fail.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types, no dependencies on other project files)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (depends on Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on both Domain and Services)","outputTokens":482,"requestId":"740B:23A6C6:152ABB5:17B5336:6A051DAA"},"id":"baffb4cb-5e1a-4c31-bb95-1cf7eec09b27","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:19.041Z","parentId":"df00cd12-471f-4e7e-8675-7bd6277df5a8"}
